comment:
* A class represents a Fast Pair device that can be discovered by multiple mediums.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: CREATOR
variables.comment: * Used to read a FastPairDevice from a Parcel.

variables.name: mModelId
variables.comment: Some OEM devices devices don't have model Id.

variables.name: mBluetoothAddress
variables.comment: Bluetooth hardware address as string. Can be read from BLE ScanResult.

methods.name: public int getTxPower()
methods.comment:
* Gets the transmit power in dBm. A value of
     * android.bluetooth.le.ScanResult#TX_POWER_NOT_PRESENT
     * indicates that the TX power is not present.

methods.name: public String getModelId()
methods.comment: * Gets the identifier of the Fast Pair device. Can be {@code null} if there is no Model ID.

methods.name: public String getBluetoothAddress()
methods.comment: * Gets the hardware address of this BluetoothDevice.

methods.name: public byte[] getData()
methods.comment:
* Gets the extra data for a Fast Pair device. Can be {@code null} if there is extra data.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public String toString()
methods.comment: * Returns a string representation of this FastPairDevice.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
